You've been working hard so far.

795
01:02:39,088 --> 01:02:42,675
You'll be someone quite influential
in your field.

796
01:03:03,988 --> 01:03:05,114
What is it?

797
01:03:05,615 --> 01:03:06,949
Why are you looking at me like that?

798
01:03:09,744 --> 01:03:12,038
I keep seeing new sides of you.

799
01:03:12,872 --> 01:03:15,583
I didn't know that
you could say things like that.

800
01:03:16,959 --> 01:03:18,669
What do you mean exactly?

801
01:03:20,129 --> 01:03:22,548
Warm, comforting,

802
01:03:23,633 --> 01:03:26,177
and encouraging words.

803
01:03:30,890 --> 01:03:32,099
Books.

804
01:03:32,183 --> 01:03:33,518
They're all in the books.

805
01:03:51,077 --> 01:03:53,454
FOOD RESEARCH INSTITUTE

806
01:04:07,009 --> 01:04:08,135
Well done.

807
01:04:08,219 --> 01:04:11,681
Thanks to you,
I could wrap up this project.

808
01:04:11,764 --> 01:04:13,683
It's you who made the decision.

809
01:04:15,685 --> 01:04:18,604
I didn't expect you to recommend
Hye-in a new workplace.

810
01:04:19,230 --> 01:04:21,107
I happened to find
the right position for her.

811
01:04:21,190 --> 01:04:23,150
Every company needs different talents.

812
01:04:23,776 --> 01:04:25,695
While some need famous stars,

813
01:04:25,778 --> 01:04:28,573
some need competent people
who aren't in the spotlight.

814
01:04:28,656 --> 01:04:30,533
Everyone has different capabilities.

815
01:04:32,118 --> 01:04:34,829
I think that I know better now

816
01:04:35,538 --> 01:04:36,539
what headhunting is.

817
01:04:37,540 --> 01:04:40,793
Finding a place where
you can demonstrate your competence

818
01:04:41,752 --> 01:04:43,254
seems like meaningful work.

819
01:04:47,592 --> 01:04:48,926
You're amazing.

820
01:04:52,179 --> 01:04:53,973
It's just work.

821
01:04:54,056 --> 01:04:55,224
No need to be so symbolic.

822
01:05:00,438 --> 01:05:02,565
Anyway, you're adapting quite quickly.

823
01:05:02,648 --> 01:05:05,109
Is it because
you work for a competent CEO?

824
01:05:07,028 --> 01:05:10,156
Actually,
adaptability is one of my strong suits.

825
01:05:12,742 --> 01:05:14,619
Let's go before it rains.

826
01:05:14,702 --> 01:05:15,745
Rain?

827
01:05:16,495 --> 01:05:18,164
But the weather is so nice.

828
01:05:25,755 --> 01:05:27,882
What? How did you know?

829
01:06:15,805 --> 01:06:17,306
What's wrong?

830
01:06:17,932 --> 01:06:19,016
Better than not having one.

831
01:06:19,684 --> 01:06:20,893
Seriously?

832
01:06:21,477 --> 01:06:23,729
- It isn't funny.
- It is.

833
01:06:28,776 --> 01:06:29,944
Let's get going.

834
01:07:37,636 --> 01:07:40,514
{\an8}<i>Ms. Kang, do you like winning that much?</i>

835
01:07:40,598 --> 01:07:42,808
{\an8}<i>I hate losing.
I want to win at everything.</i>

836
01:07:42,892 --> 01:07:45,478
{\an8}Then I'll always let you win from now on.

837
01:07:46,228 --> 01:07:48,564
{\an8}He's my candidate whom I contacted first.

838
01:07:48,647 --> 01:07:50,149
{\an8}Can you just let this one go?

839
01:07:50,232 --> 01:07:51,150
{\an8}How can you say that?!

840
01:07:51,776 --> 01:07:54,236
{\an8}<i>It still seems awkward
between Kyung-hwa and Mr. Kim.</i>

841
01:07:54,320 --> 01:07:56,405
{\an8}<i>Have a few drinks
and things will smooth over.</i>

842
01:07:56,489 --> 01:07:58,199
{\an8}- A welcoming party.
- A welcoming party?

843
01:07:58,282 --> 01:08:00,367
{\an8}Line up if you want to drink
with Ms. Kang.

844
01:08:00,451 --> 01:08:01,452
{\an8}This is a rare chance.

845
01:08:01,535 --> 01:08:02,453
{\an8}<i>Have you seen Ms. Kang?</i>

846
01:08:03,037 --> 01:08:05,623
{\an8}<i>Whenever she gets drunk,
she goes to the office.</i>

847
01:08:06,582 --> 01:08:08,000
{\an8}Ms. Kang?

848
01:08:11,378 --> 01:08:13,047
Mr. Yu.

849
01:08:20,054 --> 01:08:25,059
{\an8}Subtitle translation by: Helena Noh
